{{BLP sources|date=June 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Eliza Clark | birth_place = [[Darien, Connecticut]], U.S. | image = | occupation = Actress, playwright | spouse = {{marriage|[[Zack Whedon]]|2012}} | relatives = [[Spencer Treat Clark]] (brother) }}
'''Eliza Clark''' is an American actress and playwright. She is the sister of [[Spencer Treat Clark]]. She has acted in minor parts in movies and commercials. In 1990 she briefly played [[Jessica Buchanan]] on the [[soap opera]] ''[[One Life to Live]]''.
Clark has also directed many productions at [[Yale University]] since September 2003, including [[Wendy Wasserstein]]'s ''[[Uncommon Women and Others]]'', [[Rebecca Gilman]]'s ''[[The Glory of Living]]'' and [[Wendy MacLeod]]'s ''[[The House of Yes|House of Yes]]''.
She is also a playwright; her play, ''The Metaphysics of Breakfast'', appeared in the 2005 [[New York Fringe Festival]]. She is a member of Youngblood at the Ensemble Studio Theatre,<ref>[http://www.youngbloodnyc.org/members/clark.html Youngblood, New York] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090509193721/http://www.youngbloodnyc.org/members/clark.html |date=2009-05-09 }}</ref> which is a collective of professional playwrights. She writes for and performs in the web sitcom, ''[[Inconvenient Molly]]''.<ref>[http://justinnoble.com/inconvenientmolly/ Inconvenient Molly (a web based sitcom co-created by Eliza Clark)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130218160344/http://justinnoble.com/inconvenientmolly/ |date=2013-02-18 }}</ref>
At [[Yale University]], she was a member of the improvisational comedy group [[The Viola Question|Viola Question]], and the sketch comedy group The Fifth Humour.
Her plays have appeared at [[Provincetown Playhouse]], and in the Yale Playwrights Festival at the [[Yale Repertory Theatre|Yale Repertory Theater]], for three years in a row: "The Metaphysics of Breakfast" (2005), "Hiccup" (2006), and "Puppy." Her most recent play, "Edgewise" performed at the [[Cherry Lane Theater]] in [[New York City]] in August 2008. She is the recipient of the 2010 P73 playwriting fellowship from Page 73 Productions.
In 2010 she was on the writing staff of the [[AMC (TV channel)|AMC]] series ''[[Rubicon (TV series)|Rubicon]]''.
==Personal life== In 2012, Clark married screenwriter and film director [[Zack Whedon]]. The two met while writing for ''Rubicon''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.stylemepretty.com/2013/01/03/upstate-new-york-farm-wedding-from-tracey-buyce-photography/ |title=Upstate New York Farm Wedding from Tracey Buyce Photography|last=Capalbo|first=Abby|date=January 3, 2013|website=stylemepretty.com|accessdate=June 14, 2016}}</ref>
